  "dataFlow": "A build request enters via POST /api/build (browser form, Linear webhook, GitHub webhook, or autonomy poller). auth.py validates the session cookie (HMAC-signed token). sessions.py creates a BuildSession in _sessions (in-memory dict) and atomically persists it to app/logs/.sessions/{sid}.json. run_build() is dispatched as an asyncio task. Phase 1 (clone): git clone via subprocess into app/workspaces/{sid}/. Phase 2 (plan): PITER classifier identifies intent; relevant skills from skills/ directory and lessons from .harness/lessons.jsonl are injected into the brief. Phase 3 (generate): claude_agent_sdk.ClaudeSDKClient executes Claude against the workspace with bypassPermissions mode; streaming events are appended to session.output_lines and forwarded to any connected WebSocket or SSE client. Phase 4 (evaluate): second SDK invocation grades the git diff on 4 dimensions; score is written to session.evaluator_score; below-threshold triggers retry loop (max 2). Phase 5 (test/ship): tests run in workspace, results gated; on pass, git commit + push to origin via GITHUB_TOKEN. On completion, session status transitions to 'complete' or 'failed', persisted atomically. supabase_log.py writes a gate_check row fire-and-forget. If a Linear issue_id was associated, webhook.py (should) post back to Linear API (gap identified in gap audit). Separately, the cron engine (cron.py) fires scan/monitor/board_meeting jobs on schedule; Pi-SEO scanner writes JSON findings to .harness/scan-results/; triage engine creates Linear tickets; monitor agent writes digests to .harness/monitor-digests/. The MCP server (pi-ceo-server.js) reads .harness/ files directly from the filesystem and exposes them as tools to Claude Desktop via stdio JSON-RPC. The Telegram watchdog reads .harness/ state and sends outbound messages via urllib to api.telegram.org; inbound messages from Phill's phone arrive via Telegram webhook to POST /webhook/telegram or via polling in marathon_telegram_inbox.py.",
